"Here is your requested medium-level Python coding question:\n\n{\n\"title\": \"Maximum Sum of a Subarray\", \n\"description\": \"Given an array of integers, write a function that finds the maximum sum of any subarray within the given array. A subarray is a contiguous part of the array.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef max_sum_subarray(nums: list[int)) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the maximum sum of any subarray within the given array.\\n\", \n\"code\": \"\ndef max_sum_subarray(nums: list[int]) -> int:\n    max_sum = float('-inf')\n    current_sum = 0\n    for num in nums:\n        current_sum += num\n        if current_sum < 0:\n            current_sum = 0\n        else:\n            max_sum = max(max_sum, current_sum)\n    return max_sum\", \n\"tests\": [\"assert max_sum_subarray([-2,-3,-1]) == 2\", \"assert max_sum_subarray([1,2,3,10,1]) == 15\", \"assert max_sum_subarray([0,-1,5,-3,4,-2]) == 7\", \"assert max_sum_subarray([-1,-2,-3]) == 0\"]}"